Package org.openntf.domino.nsfdata.structs.cd

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BasicCDRecord  
    CDACTION
    The designer of a form or view may define custom actions associated with that form or view.
    CDACTIONBAR
    The designer of a form or view may define custom actions for that form or view.
    CDACTIONBAREXT
    This CD record defines the Action Bar attributes.
    CDACTIONEXT
    New field attributes have been added in Notes/Domino 6.
    CData  
    CDBAR
    This structure defines the appearance of the bar used with collapsible sections.
    CDBEGINRECORD
    This CD record defines the beginning of a series of CD Records.
    CDBITMAPHEADER
    A rich text field may contain a bitmap image.
    CDBITMAPSEGMENT
    The bitmap data is divided into segments to optimize data storage within Domino.
    CDBLOBPART
    This CD record is used in conjunction with CD record CDEVENT.
    CDBORDERINFO
    This CD record describes border information for a given table.
    CDBOXSIZE
    This CD record contains size information for a layer box.
    CDBUTTON
    This structure defines the appearance of a button in a rich text field.
    CDCAPTION
    This CD record defines the properties of a caption for a grapic [sic] record.
    CDCELLBACKGROUNDDATA
    This CD Record gives information pertaining to Background Data for a Table, specifically the 'Cell Image' repeat value.
    CDCOLOR
    This CD Record identifies the paper color for a given document.
    CDCOLORTABLE
    A color table is one of the optional records following a CDBITMAPHEADER record.
    CDDATAFLAGS
    Contains collapsible section, button type, style sheet or field limit information for Notes/Domino 6.
    CDDECSFIELD
    This CD Record gives information pertaining to data connection resource information in a field or form.
    CDDOCAUTOLAUNCH
    Structure of an on-disk autolaunch item.
    CDDOCUMENT
    This defines the structure of the document information field in a form note.
    CDEMBEDDEDCTL
    This CD record may further define attributes within a CDFIELD such as tab order.
    CDEMBEDDEDOUTLINE
    This CD Record defines the attributes of an embedded outline.
    CDEMBEDDEDVIEW
    This CD Record describes a view as an embedded element.
    CDENDRECORD
    This CD record defines the end of a series of CD records.
    CDEVENT
    This CD structure defines simple actions, formulas or LotusScript within a given image map.
    CDEVENTENTRY
    Contains additional event information for Notes/Domino 6.
    CDEXT2FIELD
    New field attributes have been added in Release 5.0 of Domino.
    CDEXTFIELD
    New field attributes have been added in Release 4.0 of Notes.
    CDFIELD
    This defines the structure of a CDFIELD record in the $Body item of a form note.
    CDFILEHEADER
    This structure is used to define a Cascading Style Sheet (CSS) that is part of a Domino database.
    CDFILESEGMENT
    This structure defines the file segment data of a Cascading Style Sheet (CSS) and follows a CDFILEHEADER structure.
    CDFONTTABLE
    This defines part of the structure of a font table item in a note.
    CDFONTTABLE.CDFACE
    This defines part of the structure of a font table item in a note.
    CDFRAME
    Frame Name String and Target Name string follow the fixed portion of this CD Record.
    CDFRAMESET
    A FRAMESETLENGTH structure will follow depending on the value found in either RowQty or ColQty.
    CDFRAMESETHEADER
    Beginning header record to both a CDFRAMESET and CDFRAME record.
    CDGRAPHIC
    The CDGRAPHIC record contains information used to control display of graphic objects in a document.
    CDHOTSPOTBEGIN
    This structure specifies the start of a "hot" region in a rich text field.
    CDHOTSPOTEND
    This structure specifies the end of a hot region in a rich text field.
    CDHRULE
    Specifies a horizontal line (editods.h)
    CDHTMLBEGIN
    Text in a rich-text field can have the "Pass-Thru HTML" attribute.
    CDHTMLEND
    Text in a rich-text field can have the "Pass-Thru HTML" attribute.
    CDIDNAME
    This CD record describes the HTML field properties, ID, Class, Style, Title, Other and Name associated for any given field defined within a Domino Form.
    CDIMAGEHEADER
    This structure is used to define a JPEG or GIF Image that is part of a Domino document.
    CDIMAGESEGMENT
    This structure defines the image segment data of a JPEG or GIF image and follows a CDIMAGEHEADER structure.
    CDINLINE
    This CD Record gives information pertaining to shared resources and/or shared code in a form.
    CDLARGEPARAGRAPH
    The 64K limit on paragraphs has been removed in Notes/Domino 6.
    CDLAYER
    The definition for a layer on a form is stored as CD records in the $Body item of the form note.
    CDLAYOUT
    The definition for a layout region on a form is stored as CD records in the $Body item of the form note.
    CDLAYOUTBUTTON
    A button in a layout region of a form is defined by a CDLAYOUTBUTTON record.
    CDLAYOUTEND
    The CDLAYOUTEND record marks the end of the elements defining a layout region within a form.
    CDLAYOUTFIELD
    A field in a layout region of a form is defined by a CDLAYOUTFIELD record.
    CDLAYOUTGRAPHIC
    A graphical element in a layout region of a form is defined by a CDLAYOUTGRAPHIC record.
    CDLAYOUTTEXT
    A text element in a layout region of a form is defined by a CDLAYOUTTEXT record.
    CDLINK2
    This structure implements a document link in a rich text field.
    CDLSOBJECT
    The CD record contains Lotus Script object code.
    CDOLEBEGIN
    This structure specifies the start of an OLE Object.
    CDOLEEND
    This structure specifies the end of an OLE Object in a rich text field.
    CDOLEOBJ_INFO
    This structure specifies a connection to an OLE object.
    CDPABDEFINITION
    This structure specifies a format for paragraphs in a rich-text field.
    CDPABFORMULAREF
    Starting in Release 4.0 of Notes, a paragraph may have an associated formula that determines when the paragraph is to be hidden.
    CDPABHIDE
    This record contains the "Hide When" formula for a paragraph attributes block.
    CDPABREFERENCE
    This structure is placed at the start of each paragraph in a rich-text field, and specifies which CDPABDEFINITION is used as the format for the paragraph.
    CDPARAGRAPH
    This structure defines the start of a new paragraph within a rich-text field.
    CDPATTERNTABLE
    A pattern table is one of the optional records following a CDBITMAPHEADER record.
    CDPATTERNTABLE.Pattern
    The pattern table consists of a record header, which identifies this as a Pattern Table record, followed by up to 64 pattern table entries.
    CDPDEF_ACTION
    This doesn't appear in the API documentation, but is presumably part of Composite Apps.
    CDPDEF_MAIN
    This doesn't appear in the API documentation, but is presumably part of Composite Apps.
    CDPDEF_PROPERTY
    This doesn't appear in the API documentation, but is presumably part of Composite Apps.
    CDPDEF_TYPE
    This doesn't appear in the API documentation, but is presumably part of Composite Apps.
    CDPLACEHOLDER
    A CDPLACEHOLDER record stores additional information about various embedded type CD records, such as CDEMBEDDEDCTL, CDEMBEDDEDOUTLINE and other embedded CD record types defined in HOTSPOTREC_TYPE_xxx.
    CDPOSITIONING
    This CD record contains position information for a layer box.
    CDPRETABLEBEGIN
    This CD record provides additional table properties, expanding the information provided in CDTABLEBEGIN.
    CDRecord  
    CDREGIONBEGIN
    This CD Record is used within mail templates.
    CDREGIONEND  
    CDRESOURCE
    This CD record defines a resource within a database.
    CDSTYLENAME
    This structure stores the style name for a Paragraph Attributes Block (PAB).
    CDTABLEBEGIN
    This structure specifies the beginning of a table.
    CDTABLECELL
    This structure specifies the cell of a table.
    CDTABLEDATAEXTENSION
    This record was added because the Pre Table Begin Record can not be expanded and R6 required more data to be stored.
    CDTABLEEND
    This structure specifies the end of a table.
    CDTABLELABEL
    This CD Record further defines information for a table.
    CDTABLEROWHEIGHT
    This CD record describes the Row Height property for a table.
    CDTARGET
    The CDTARGET structure specifies the target (ie: the frame) where a resource link hotspot is to be displayed.
    CDTEXT
    This structure defines the start of a run of text in a rich-text field.
    CDVERTICALALIGN
    This CD record allows for additional information to be provided for a graphic.
    CDWINMETAHEADER
    Identifies a Windows Graphics Device Interface (GDI) metafile embedded in a rich text field.
    CDWINMETASEG
    A portion of a Windows GDI metafile.
